The kindergarten is also part of offices that included architects.
the administrative building Avriopoint de Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch. Design.
No one could have expected him to also house a mini kindergarten with everything he needed - colored walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October of last year, children can become employees of Arch. design.
The company of architectural projects Arch. Design., whose workshops have produced a large number of constructions in Brno, has imagined its mini kindergarten since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
It employs about 90 people, especially from the age of child-making, and it was important for architects and project leaders to be able to return to work quickly.
Along with time contracts reduced, the kindergarten is a bonus offered to its employees by Arch. Design. within the framework of its social program.
The builders and architects thus have the opportunity to combine work with care for children.
It is the employees of Arch.Design.They themselves have imagined this kindergarten and with the support of the management they have been able to obtain an endowment from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini maternity school is funded by the European Social Fund through the operational programme of human resources and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to the funding facilities (up to 2.8 thousand Czech krona), they were able to purchase equipment and equipment and after two years provide qualified personnel and start-up.
After the use of the two-year funding facility, the company Arch. Design. has the obligation after 3 years to operate the maternal mini school on its own funds.
The preparation of the project lasted one year and it was the Economy rating company that helped to apply for staffing.
Child care is provided by qualified staff, a nurse and a kindergarten teacher care for children all day. Children can go to kindergarten without age limitation but they are over three for most.
As a \"Ministry of Mother School\" there can be only 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more who replace each other.
The functioning of the school is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use this school without regard for the hierarchical position.
Although it is an individual care and education, the programme of the mini-school is comparable to that for preschool education.
Children don't just play it, but quality education is also assured - from the beginning to the preparation of school benches English is taught.
The class is equipped not only with imaginative toys and games but also with a computer that children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents can at any time control their children and do not have the stress of a delay to go look for children in a school away from their parents' workplace.
Parents therefore use their working time in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that a natural relationship of loyalty between the employee and the employer is created.
Arch.Design.s is thus registered among companies that offer a choice bonus for recruiting new employees and who are friendly to the family and through this program reinforces the marketing of HR.
The bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Take a look in Gaudi's interiors.
The roof resembles the back of a prehistoric saurian, the stairway to a vertebral column of dinosaurs and balconies to open fish mouths.
This is the Casa Battlo house in Barcelona by architect Antoni Gaudi.
Due to its organic forms, the house received from the premises the nickname House in bone.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stones, fragments of tiles and mosaics, facade reminiscent of scales and everywhere present of curves, here is all that is ypic for Art Nouveau d'Antoni Gaudi.
The front façade of the house runs its dream lines, its pleasing colours and textures that remind nature and animals.
In a more detailed observation we see geometry, rhythm and order thought precisely.
In the night the facade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brightness of the colors is reinforced.
The winding and twisting of the shapes also appears in the interiors with the same measure.
The wood copies in waves the frames of windows, the balustrades, the decorative elements of the doors, the eyepiece and the lamps.
The Battlo house that stands in the Eixample district in Passeig de Gracia shopping street by number. 43, was born of the construction of a 1877 house of architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took place for two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a wealthy entrepreneur, first insisted on demolishing the old building and building a new one but quickly accepted Gaudi's idea of an unusual and better market reconstruction.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as a multiple dwelling house was not thought of by Gaudi alone.
Architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It is precisely on his project that decorations are given for an apartment representing the owner of the building and the use of the mosaic for the facade.
Other artists and creators also worked for the facade.
The joint work for the plans of Casa Battlo began with successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of the house of Gaudi Casa Mila and Guell Park in which there are other works of Gaudi.
The premises have nicknamed the house hot right after its completion because of its organic forms - the House in the bone -
Others, in view of the specific mechanism of opening windows, called it the house that dances -
It is said that at the top of the construction there is a sword similar to that of Saint Georges the patron of Catalonia.
Other elements of sculpture of construction contain hidden religious motifs.
Gaudi thought for the house a unique system in its central heating time, with air vents and typical fireplaces.
Their 45 degree inclination seems strange.
During the creation Gaudi absolutely did not comply with the construction guidelines and did not allow itself to be hindered by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained from the city the building permit, knowing, of course, that the data on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the completion the municipal council was horrified and demanded modifications.
He did not like, for example, the members of the municipal council that the pillars of construction stack on the public sidewalk.
There was never any change, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the city's call Josep Battlo asked for (and got satisfaction) permission to rent the top two floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room and in the third one bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented at a jewelery.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase that allows access to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were cancelled by the basic elements of reconstruction and their replacement by curved walls.
Gaudi also worked on the modern concept of space liaison.
The common part can be connected completely by opening the doors of the halls and the high society can communicate comfortably or limit private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with Gaudi's reconstruction has also received new facades a non-traditional roof and two floors in addition.
Gaudi's game with light is also impressive, blue and white glass tiles with which the inner courtyard is decorated and with light shafts.
The two-coloured game gives maximum light on all floors of the house.
It was simply enough to bet on the principle that white reflects more than the dark that instead absorbs the rays of the sun.
The Casa Battlo house which was registered in 2005 in the Unesco World Heritage Fund may be visited by each one.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and beautiful apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous creator.
They continued the visits because they found that it was a lucrative business and they extended the field of visits to common spaces and at the barn, including roof terraces.
The entrance ticket in the monument is not really expensive and costs 16.50 euros; students, retirees, groups and tourist card holders have 20% discount.
The sum is still above the entry price in the other buildings of Gaudi in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic towers, you must quickly find a friend among the inhabitants of the building and visit the house completely.
