Apparatus to follow people are increasingly being asked by parents who want to monitor their children.
Fear for their child causes more and more people to think about monitoring them through a GPS.
The system, put in place at the beginning to search for cars can also be used to trace the movement of people and help in some cases as by example that of little Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as large as a match box but will soon be the size of a watch.
The case of Little Anicka has moved a large number of people and they have begun to seek ways to protect their children better.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
\"We are trying to tell everyone that it is not espionage but only another way to reduce the likelihood of another tragedy,\" says Petr Pilin of the company Macro Weil, who is one of the suppliers of tracking devices on the Czech market.
\"I admit that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting it in the bag of a person who is not aware of it, but I have not yet encountered such cases\"
“Most people are customers who actually buy the product for security reasons,” Pilin adds.
According to him, children should always know for what purpose the box is used and how to use it in case of an emergency.
The child psychologist, Dana Bockova, draws attention to the fact that if the child does not want to bring something like this to him, he will get rid of it.
'And even the smallest can show great creativity when it comes to deliberately getting rid of something when they don't want to be under control.'
“Portable phones, which can be cut like these tracking devices, have already led parents to long expectations,” says Bockova.
According to her, the fact that this type of device can help in the event of aggression is very questionable.
\"If it is a prepared kidnapping, the author will do everything to make sure that the child does not have an electronic device that can locate it.\"
\"Now it's the phone.\"
\"As soon as the tracking equipment develops, they (criminals) will also look for it as the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign\"
“In such cases criminals will always be ahead of the police,” said the psychologist.
It acknowledges that such devices can help when an attack is not prepared by a pedophile.
According to Robert Cech of RC Monitoring, who offers tracking services for both cars and people, he says that having this type of device can help, even if it is destroyed in the case of an aggression.
‘The device may be set up in such a way that it is on a regular basis after a specified period of time.’
‘In case the device is destroyed, the last position of the person concerned remains the same.’
'The most expensive devices also have an inclinometer that immediately signals the position of the person who has slipped and is in an elongated position without moving,' says Cech.
According to him, smartphones that are equipped with a navigation system can offer comparable service after having formed it with a special prologic.
The problem with the current tracking systems is that it is a device similar to the one carried on the pendant of the size of an allumette box or the smallest telephone devices.
We can always lose them.
According to Pilina of Macro Weil, this is why tests are currently being carried out to make devices that look like common digital watches.
‘This will have the advantage that the potential aggressor will not be able to recognize the tracer’
\"Or it will come to light after some time, which will have given the police a little more time,\" he added.
Whether the tracer is developed as a bracelet or pendant, it will always use the same technology as to trace cars.
This is a combination of one-position acquisition systems using the GPS (which is commonly used as self-navigation) and a function of a mobile phone that alerts the current position of a vehicle.
