14 alleged drug traffickers arrested
A dozen searches were conducted in Estrie on Wednesday as part of the dismantling of a cannabis production and sale network.
Fourteen people have been arrested and will face various charges.
The searches took place in Sherbrooke, Orford and Stoke, mostly in places that would have been used for drug production.
\"About 750 cannabis plants, four kilos of hasch, money and equipment used for production were seized,\" said Louis-Philippe Ruel, spokesperson for the Sûreté du Québec.
In all, eleven men and three women were arrested, including the two leaders assumed in this network, two Sherbrooke men.
Arrested persons were due to appear at the Sherbrooke courthouse within hours of their arrest.
They could face accusations of cannabis production, possession in order to deal with trafficking, conspiracy and theft of services, among others.
These searches were conducted following a long-term investigation, which lasted about a year.
\"It was information received from the public that allowed us to make these arrests,\" Mr. Ruel said.
Some 70 police officers from the Regional Investigation Module of the Estrie de la Sûreté du Québec, the Sherbrooke Police Service and the Memphremagog Police Region participated in this police operation.
